[assistant] Created a minimal RP2040 breakout in `index.circuit.tsx:1` with a USB-C connector, RP2040 MCU, one status LED, and two decoupling capacitors, all using local/JLCPCB-imported components from `imports/RP2040.tsx:1`, `imports/TYPE_C_16PIN_2MD_073_.tsx:1`, `imports/KT_0603R.tsx:1`, `imports/A_0603WAF1002T5E.tsx:1`, and `imports/CC0603KRX7R9BB104.tsx:1`.
- Set `routingDisabled` on the board in `index.circuit.tsx:9` so autorouting stays off as requested.
- Kept the design intentionally minimal: USB VBUS feeds `VREG_IN`, USB D+/D- go straight to the RP2040 USB pins, all I/O/analog supply pins tie to `V3_3`, DVDD pins tie to the internal regulator rail, and GPIO25 drives the LED through a series resistor.
- Used sensible assumptions for a stripped-down breakout: no external flash, crystal, boot/reset buttons, CC pull-downs, or headers, which keeps the board minimal but not a complete bootable/reference RP2040 implementation.
- Ran `tsci build --site --use-cdn-javascript`; generated output is in `dist/`, including `dist/index/circuit.json`.
- Ran `tsci snapshot`; snapshot artifacts are available at `__snapshots__/index.circuit-pcb.snap.svg` and `__snapshots__/index.circuit-schematic.snap.svg`.
